gomodel:SYNGO_2220  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" , "Rationale: LRRC4b was enriched in postsynaptic density fractions.\n\n15/01/2018 Pim\n- Postsynaptic (as opposed to presynatic) localization of the LRRC4b protein is evidenced by the experiments in Fig.4 that show \"Direct aggregation of NGL-3 on the surface of dendrites induces coclustering of excitatory postsynaptic proteins.\" and the known interaction of NGL-3 with PSD-95 (see additional literature).\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Figure legend\nFigure 2: Expression patterns of NGL-3 proteins in rat brain." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2220" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

